The Base Account SDK provides two primary methods for implementing Base Pay: the pay() function for initiating payments and the getPaymentStatus() function for checking transaction status. Below is a step-by-step guide to integrating Base Pay into a web application, based on the official documentation.

Client-Side Implementation (Browser SDK)To initiate a payment, developers can use the pay() function. Hereâ€™s an example of how to trigger a USDC payment:javascript

import { pay, getPaymentStatus } from '@base-org/account';

// Trigger a payment
try {
  const payment = await pay({
    amount: '1.00', // USD amount (converted to USDC internally)
    to: '0xRecipient', // Recipient address
    testnet: true // Set to false for Mainnet
  });

  // Poll for payment status
  const { status } = await getPaymentStatus({
    id: payment.id,
    testnet: true // Must match the testnet setting in pay()
  });

  if (status === 'completed') {
    console.log('ðŸŽ‰ Payment settled');
  }
} catch (error) {
  console.error(`Payment failed: ${error.message}`);
}

